# Step 3 — Our First Business Event
 

In production we send **Business Objects**.

Let's create an Order Event.

```java
package com.example.orderservice.dto;

import lombok.AllArgsConstructor;
import lombok.Data;
import lombok.NoArgsConstructor;

import java.math.BigDecimal;

@Data
@NoArgsConstructor
@AllArgsConstructor
public class OrderEvent {

    private Long orderId;

    private Long customerId;

    private String productName;

    private Integer quantity;

    private BigDecimal amount;
}
```

---

## Why DTO?

Interview Question

**Why don't we send Entity objects?**

Answer

Because Kafka messages are part of our communication contract.

Sending JPA entities:

* Couples services tightly
* Exposes unnecessary fields
* Causes serialization issues
* Makes schema evolution harder

Instead we send DTO/Event objects.

